# AI agent rules

- AI agents interpret, summarize, compare, and draft; they do not create quantitative truth.
- Agents consume approved context and domain events, read through ports, and invoke Application use cases for mutations.
- Require traceable inputs, model identity, prompt/version metadata, outputs, and linked evidence.
- Distinguish facts, calculations, assumptions, and model interpretation in every durable artifact.
- Never allow an agent to bypass validation, guardrails, risk review, authorization, or state transitions.
- Design for timeout, retry, idempotency, provider failure, human review, and reproducible re-evaluation.
